A body of a man has been found in Keiyo South, Elgeyo Marakwet county on Friday. Authorities said the deceased may have been murdered on Thursday night and his body dumped at Kapchebelel sub-location. Area assistant Chief David Rono said the body was discovered by villagers who going to their farms. Rono said the corpse had bruises on the neck, an indication that he may have been strangled. He said the police are holding Stephen Kipkurui, 22, in connection with the death. Kipkurui was spotted leaving Flax trading centre with the deceased on Thursday evening. The body has been taken to Moi Teaching and Referral Hospital mortuary for an autopsy.  Click here for the latest political news